Class NotationStack<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • NotationStack<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - A DataType you want to store in the NotationStack
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    StackInterface<T>

    public class NotationStack<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements StackInterface<T>
    NotationStack is a data structure that takes in any data and puts them in a Stack. A stack works with the concept of Last In, First out. Meaning that when you add something to the stack, it gets put on the top of the stack and when you want to take something out, the top gets taken off. You can work with this data by calling its toString method.
    Author:
    Michael Amaya
